description: Numbers n such that n remains prime through 2 iterations of function f(x) = 10x + 3.
comments: n, 10*n+3 and 100*n+33 are primes. [From _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 04 2010]
prog: (MAGMA) [n: n in [1..100000] | IsPrime(n) and IsPrime(10*n+3) and IsPrime(100*n+33)] [From _Vincenzo Librandi_, Aug 04 2010]
author: _David W. Wilson_
